theorem closure_diff_frontier_eq_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    closure A \ frontier A = interior A := by
  apply subset_antisymm
  · -- `closure A \ frontier A ⊆ interior A`
    intro x hx
    rcases hx with ⟨hx_cl, hx_notFront⟩
    by_cases hx_int : x ∈ interior A
    · exact hx_int
    · -- If `x ∉ interior A` but `x ∈ closure A`, then `x` lies in the frontier,
      -- contradicting `hx_notFront`.
      have hFront : x ∈ frontier A := by
        have : x ∈ closure A \ interior A := And.intro hx_cl hx_int
        simpa [frontier_eq_closure_diff_interior] using this
      exact (hx_notFront hFront).elim
  · -- `interior A ⊆ closure A \ frontier A`
    intro x hx_int
    have hx_cl : x ∈ closure A := subset_closure (interior_subset hx_int)
    -- Points of `interior A` do not belong to the frontier.
    have hx_notFront : x ∉ frontier A := by
      have hSub : frontier (A : Set X) ⊆ (interior A)ᶜ :=
        frontier_subset_compl_interior (A := A)
      intro hFront
      exact (hSub hFront) hx_int
    exact And.intro hx_cl hx_notFront

theorem frontier_diff_subset_union {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    frontier (A \ B) ⊆ frontier A ∪ frontier B := by
  -- First rewrite the difference as an intersection and apply the existing lemma
  have h :
      frontier (A \ B) ⊆ frontier A ∪ frontier (Bᶜ) := by
    simpa [Set.diff_eq] using
      (frontier_inter_subset (A := A) (B := Bᶜ))
  -- Replace `frontier (Bᶜ)` with `frontier B`
  simpa [frontier_compl_eq_frontier (A := B)] using h
